Sometimes violence is the only solution that works, namely a swift and painful execution.  If enough of these fucks were put to death it would help weed out the gene pool and it would teach fear to those who need to learn it the most.<br>
<br>
Fear is a wonderful teacher, how long has it been since you purposely touched anything hot?<br>
<br>
This 'stuff&quot; happens because we allow it to, in the other thread where the woman ignored her child to play EQ and lost that child when it locked itself in a car Tibult made the remark that the laws are written to protect the guilty rather than the innocent.<br>
<br>
That's EXACTLY the problem, we've become too soft in our dealings with criminals.  We see things like this and rather than placing the blame squarely on the woman who tried to bake her baby in the oven we look for causes, for reasons, for excuses.<br>
<br>
There IS no excuse for doing something like that to a baby.  There is only our failure as a society for allowing these types of activies to become an accepted norm.  Toughen the laws and the penalties for breaking them and people will fear to do so unless they are so fucking stupid that they do not care.  I do not know about any of you but the sooner we identify and remove those people that don't care from our midst the safer I will begin to feel.<br>
<br>
This woman tried to bake her child.  There's no fucking way any amount of therapy fixes that mental state.  You put that animal down so it can never hurt any one else again.  <br>
<br>
Anything less is asking for a repeat offense and we then have no one but ourselves to blame for letting it happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=surrealle>Surrealle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>*wags tail*</span><br>  Posts: 406<br> <font color=#330000>(8/24/03 9:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sad story</span><hr size=1> I wasn't saying she should just get therapy; in fact I said she DID deserve to be punished. My point is that all the ideas you guys are coming up with for &quot;justice&quot;, and I use the word sparingly, are just creepy. Not only with this thread--look back at the threads about drunk drivers, the woman that pulled the prank on those parents, etc. IMO anything so much more drastic than like, &quot;an eye for an eye, tooth for a tooth&quot; justice system just seems like malice on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>our</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> part. <br>
